tp:treatment-sec.p:
Live female (
Fig. 4 D
): scales on trunk and head pale grey-brown, darker on dorsum and lighter to silver on venter. Scales with dark grey-brown margin, creating reticulation on trunk. Light blue iridescence on trunk and opercular region. Iris silver. All fins hyaline.

The increasing pressure on land and water resources of wetlands will continue to result in habitat degradation and represent and important threat to the species, raising vulnerability in terms of conservation status. In combination with its seasonal life cycle in ephemeral habitats, its dependence on the clay-rich vertisol-type substratum for embryonic development makes the species more exposed to threats (
Nagy & Watters 2020
).
